ve":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"Issue fixed by patch for EUCA-11175.\r\n\r\nVersion of Eucalyptus:\r\n{code}\r\ncommit ef49872a74d01a70673136dcce04355ec5da0d11\r\nAuthor: Sang-Min Park <smpark.uva@gmail.com>\r\nDate:   Wed Jul 22 14:57:19 2015 -0700\r\n\r\n    EUCA-11175\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n*Steps*\r\n\r\n# Set up Eucalyptus 4.1.2 cloud via source - [environment.yml|http://jenkins.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com/job/Quick%20Launch%20Maint-4.1/149/artifact/environment.yml/*view*/]\r\n# Enable Eucalyptus DNS\r\n# Create EBS-backed EMI, and launch an instance using block-device-mapping flag for ephemeral\r\n# After the instance has successfully launched, use euca-create-image to create an EMI from the instance.\r\n# Run TerminateInstances against the EBS-backed instance used with CreateImage\r\n# Launch another instance from the EBS-backed EMI with block device mapping flag for adding a 5 gig volume\r\n# Wait 10 seconds, then run TerminateInstances against the EBS-backed instance used with CreateImage\r\n# Launch another instance from the EBS-backed EMI using block-device-mapping flag for ephemeral\r\n# Run TerminateInstances against the EBS-backed instance used with CreateImage\r\n# Notice all EMIs associated with terminated instances go to 'failed' state\r\n{code}\r\n[root@d-41 ~]# euca-describe-images emi-e705de5e emi-8410c500 emi-d60a94c1\r\nIMAGE\temi-8410c500\t256644401136/ubuntu-trusty-amd64-ebs-hvm-v2\t256644401136\tfailed\tprivate\tx86_64\tmachine\t\t\t\tebs\thvm\r\nBLOCKDEVICEMAPPING\tEPHEMERAL\t/dev/sdb\tephemeral0\r\nIMAGE\temi-d60a94c1\t256644401136/ubuntu-trusty-amd64-ebs-hvm-v4\t256644401136\tfailed\tprivate\tx86_64\tmachine\t\t\t\tebs\thvm\r\nBLOCKDEVICEMAPPING\tEPHEMERAL\t/dev/sdb\tephemeral0\r\nIMAGE\temi-e705de5e\t256644401136/ubuntu-trusty-amd64-ebs-hvm-v3\t256644401136\tfailed\tprivate\tx86_64\tmachine\t\t\t\tebs\thvm\r\nBLOCKDEVICEMAPPING\tEPHEMERAL\t/dev/sdb\tephemeral0\r\n{code}","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.ne